title.narrative: SOCIAL PROTECTION SYSTEM

description.narrative: Strengthened national and subnational capacity to develop and implement a child sensitive, inclusive and integrated social protection system, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Child poverty in all its forms is reduced through quality, evidence-based policies, programmes and budgets for all children, especially the most marginalized, at national and subnational levels

title.narrative: Strengthened national and subnational capacity to develop and implement a child sensitive, inclusive and integrated socialprotection system

description.narrative: UNICEF supported;the mainland;Government;in developing the coordination mechanism and monitoring framework;which are;key;instruments;for;the;National;social protection policy. The;Government;has;started the process of updating the;policy.;In Zanzibar, the social protection implementation plan was reviewed, and UNICEF continues to support the;implementation;Government coordination mechanism. The Productive Social Safety Net – PSSN II program started targeting the remaining 30 percent in mainland and Zanzibar that were not covered in PSSN I. The program;is expected to enroll;an;estimated;400,000 new beneficiaries. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:22/12/2021
